Recipe.create!(name:"Almond Crescents (Vanilla Kipferl)", ingredients:"1 cup blanched almonds toasted (or ground already)*, 2/3 cup granulated sugar, 1 cup butter (2 sticks), softened - no substitutions, 2 1/2 cups flour, 3 large egg yolks (use the whites for Schaum cookies or divinity), 6 packages (0.32 oz each) vanilla sugar (about 3/4 cup)*, 3/4 cup powdered sugar", directions:"In food processor - blend almonds and 1/3 cup sugar until finely ground (I used 2 packets of already ground almonds), In separate bowl beat butter and other 1/3 cup sugar until creamy, Add egg yolks and blend well, Add almond/sugar mixture - blend well, Add flour and stir just until blended, With hands - knead dough a few times to press together, Shape dough by level teaspoons into 1 1/2 inch crescents(dough may be crumbly - heat of hands will help it stick together), Place crescents on cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart, Bake at 325 for 15 minutes or until slightly browned, In a medium bowl blend vanilla sugar and powdered sugar(roll warm cookies in this mixture one or two at a time and then set on a wire rack to cool), Makes about 9 1/2 dozen", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Almond Snowdrifts", ingredients:"2 egg whites, 1 cup sugar, 1/4 tsp salt, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 1/2 cups finely chopped unblanched almonds, 1 tbl flour", directions:"Beat egg whites until stiff, Beat in sugar a little at a time-beating well after each addition, Fold in salt, vanilla, almonds and flour - blend well, Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a lightly floured baking sheet - will spread, Bake at 325 for 15 to 17 minutes, Remove from baking sheets while still warm, A very thin crispy cookie - lace  like", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from Aunt Linda (Klasek) 1977"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Apple Crisp", ingredients:"3 lb bag of apples (granny smith, mccintosh or paula reds), 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tbls flour, 1 cup oatmeal, 1 cup flour, 1 stick butter or margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar", directions:"Core apples and cut into slices (no need to peel), Mix 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tbls flour, stir into sliced apples to coat, pour into a buttered 9 x 13 pan, Cover with topping - oatmeal, flour, butter and brown sugar mixed until crumbly, Bake at 350 for 30 minutes", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Baked Corn Casserole", ingredients:"1 can cream style corn, 1 can whole kernel corn - drained, 1 egg, 1/2 pack Ritz crackers - crushed fine, dash of black pepper, dash of salt, 1 tbl sugar", directions:"Set aside about 2 tbls of the crushed Ritz to sprinkle on top, Mix together all other ingredients including the remaining Ritz crackers, Pour into a buttered casserole dish, Sprinkle the reserved Ritz over the top, Cover and bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees, Remove cover and bake 10 minutes more", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"Recipe from Karen (Kay) Healy(my 'big' sister)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Banana Nut Bread", ingredients:"1/2 cup margarine, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 2 eggs well beaten, 2 cups flour, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 tsp baking soda, 1/2 cup sour milk ( fresh with 1 tsp vinegar and let stand for 5 minutes), 1 cup mashed banana, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts", directions:"Blend all ingredients together, Grease and flour a 5 x 7 loaf pan, Bake at 350 for 60 minutes", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from Faye Stepp that I have made quite a number of times."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Biscuits", ingredients:"2 1/2 cups self-rising flour, 1/4 cup oil, 1 cup Buttermilk, 2/3 cup water", directions:"Mix well and turn out onto floured board, Knead a few times, Oil the baking sheet enough so that you can turn each biscuit over to coat both sides, Pinch off enough for each biscuit or flatten dough and cut, Place into pan close together - sides touching - remember to roll over each biscuit in oil, Bake at 400 for 12 to 14 minutes", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"Recipe from Aunt Lois"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Donuts(Biscuit)", ingredients:"1 can biscuits - any style, large frying pan or dutch oven (big pan no matter what you use), 3in cooking oil in pan", directions:"Heat oil over medium heat - tricky - too hot and the donuts will burn / too cold and they will be raw in center, poke a hole into each biscuit and stretch out the ring somewhat, drop 2 or 3 at a time into the oil, allow to brown on bottom side and then flip over, when completely brown - remove from pan and drain on paper towels, Roll in granulated sugar or cinnamon sugar or powdered sugar while still warm, You can make sticks, twists and little donut hole size bites, too - they don't have to be a ring donut", category:"Dessert", contributor:"These recipes were created as a result of tight budgets and continued out of tradition and convenience, Every Christmas 'the boys', Matthew, Chris and Steve have the donuts at their Dad's as tradition"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pizza(Buscuit)", ingredients:"1 can biscuits, 1 small can pizza sauce, mozzarella cheese, pepperoni", directions:"lay out biscuits, flatten with rolling pin or press flat with fingers, put 1 tsp sauce on each biscuit and spread to edges, place pepperoni on sauce, cover with mozzarella, Bake at 400 for 8 to 10 minutes", category:"Dinner", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Bleu Cheese Tenderloin", ingredients:"8 oz tenderloin steaks, 3 oz bleu cheese crumbles for each steak, 3 oz Red Wine Demi Glace for each steak, Demi Glace, heat 2 cups Red Wine and simmer until reduced to 1/2 cup, alcohol will evaporate and consistency will be like syrup", directions:"Broil or grill steaks - add salt & pepper to taste, When nearly done top with bleu cheese to melt, Serve with demi glace", category:"Dinner", contributor:"from Candi's wedding(Candi's was served with grilled white asparagus and mashed potatoes, Mom got the recipe from the Chef)")
Recipe.create!(name:"Buckeyes - Ohio State Candy", ingredients:"1 cup peanut Butter, 1/4 cup margarine, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 1/2 cup powdered sugar (might need more. Just depend on how mixture feels), 1/2 cup flour, 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips - melted", directions:"Line two cookie sheets with waxed paper or parchment paper, Beat peanut butter, margarine and vanilla, Gradually beat in powdered sugar and flour, Roll into balls, Chill for 1 hour, With a toothpick - spear balls one at a time and dip 3/4 of the way into melted chocolate, Put back on waxed paper - chocolate side down, Chill 15 minutes until chocolate is set, Makes 60, To melt chocolate chips: use a double boiler method adding 1 tsp shortening, or melt in 20 second intervals in the microwave, also with 1 tsp shortening, stir every 20 seconds until melted, Never add water or the chocolate will seize and be a clumpy mess", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Buttercream Frosting(Use for icing cakes and also making decorations like roses)", ingredients:"1 cup shortening, 2 lbs. powdered sugar, 1/2 tsp popcorn salt, 1/4 cup milk - may need more but add in 1 tablespoon at a time, 1 tsp clear almond extract (Mamaw's recipe) (may use clear vanilla if desired)", directions:"Beat for 5 to 10 minutes until fluffy.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Buttercream Frosting(Use for icing cakes or filling cookies - stays soft / does not crust over)", ingredients:"2 cups shortening (or 1 cup shortening and 1 cup unsalted butter), 2 lbs. powdered sugar, 1/2 tsp popcorn salt, 1/4 cup milk - may need more but add in 1 tablespoon at a time, 1 tsp. clear vanilla (or clear almond)", directions:"Beat for 10 minutes until fluffy, Add 1 bar of cream cheese to either recipe above for a cream cheese frosting, Must be refrigerated if it contains cream cheese, Good for carrot cake or red velvet cake, Try other extracts like lemon, orange, cherry, raspberry or Wilton's clear butter flavoring", category:"Dessert", contributor:"")
Recipe.create!(name:"Vanilla Butter Nut Poundcake", ingredients:"1/2 cup shortening, 2 sticks margarine, 3 cups sugar, 3 cups flour, 1 cup milk, 1/4 tsp salt, 6 eggs, 3 tsp Butter Nut flavoring ( flavoring from Superior Prod. Co. ~ Charlotte, N.C. )", directions:"Cream shortening and margarine, Add sugar and salt - beat well, Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition, Add flavoring to milk and then add to batter alternately with flour, Grease and flour a bundt pan ( or tube pan ), Bake at 325 for 1 1/2 hours", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cabbage Rolls", ingredients:"2 lbs. ground chuck, 1 large onion - chopped fine, 2 eggs, 1 cup rice - instant type (not cooked), dash of each salt & pepper, 2 slices white bread, 1 can of tomatoes (16 oz size) - diced (you are going to sprinkle on a dusting of sugar when you assemble), 1 can of saur kraut (16 oz size) - drained, 1 can of V-8 juice (48 oz large can), 1/2 cup water, 1 head of cabbage - large / loose leaf - (you will use it all so save those outer leaves)", directions:"Prep Cabbage: Wash cabbage and trim off the stem end, Fill a large pot (Dutch oven or larger) about 2/3 full of water and heat to a simmer, Place whole cabbage and outer leaves into the simmering water, cover and let steam a few minutes, Remove and drain leaves as they get tender enough to pull off - you will need about 10 to 12 total, Remove the rest of the head of cabbage and let it cool down - toss out the water Prep Meat: In a large bowl mix together the ground beef, onion and egg.  Then mix in the rice, salt & pepper, Soak the two slices of white bread with water, gently squeeze out excess and then crumble in mixture, Make medium size egg shaped meatballs - 10 to 12 of them - and wrap each one in a cabbage leaf Assemble: In the same large (now empty) pot, pour in 1/2 cup water, Chop remainder of cabbage head in large shreds and line bottom of pan, Place cabbage rolls across pan on top of shredded cabbage leaving space between the rolls, Layer on the kraut next across the whole pan, place diced tomato on next layer (dust with a bit of sugar), Pour V-8 over all.  Salt and pepper to taste.  Bring to a boil then lower to a simmer and cook until done", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Janet's, One of my earliest memories was when Mom made these.  Mike, Pat and I thought she was trying to poison us with all that stinky kraut and cabbage.  Then she started wrapping a dime in foil and putting it in the center of only a few of the cabbage rolls.  The deal was - you had to eat the one you took from the pan plus some kraut and cabbage.  If you were lucky, you got a dime on the first pick.  Not so lucky, the choice was yours, live without the dime or try again but you had to finish it if you picked it out of the pan. Remember, candy was 2 for a penny so a dime made you rich.  Needless to say we all learned to like these and they have become very popular at family gatherings.  They are Matthew's favorite.  Mom said if you have any questions to just call her."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cannolli  Cake", ingredients:"Filling: 1 tub 16 oz Ricotta cheese - 75% moisture(allow to drain in a strainer for a couple of hours or overnight), 3 tbls orange liqueur or orange extract, 1/4 cup granulated sugar, 1/2 cup heavy whipping cream, 1/2 cup coarsely chopped mixed candied fruit ( citron ), 1/2 cup mini chocolate chips. Sponge Cake Roll: 4 eggs - room temperature, 2/3 cup sugar, 1 tsp vanilla, 2/3 cup flour, 1 tbl freshly grated orange zest, Powdered sugar for dusting", directions:"Filling: Beat ricotta, orange flavoring and sugar until smooth, In another bowl beat whipping cream until soft peaks stage, Fold in ricotta mixture, candied fruit and mini chips. Sponge Cake Roll: Beat eggs and sugar on high speed for 5 to 6 minutes until tripled in volume, Beat in vanilla, Fold in flour and orange zest - gently, Spread into a well greased, parchment lined 15 x 10 baking pan, Bake at 350 for 13 to 15 minutes, Invert onto powdered sugar covered kitchen towel and roll up tightly, When completely cool - fill with cannolli filling - reroll and dust with powdered sugar", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Caprese Salad", ingredients:"4 plum (Roma) tomatoes, 1 container fresh mozzarella balls - water packed, Fresh Basil leaves, Olive oil, salt and pepper", directions:"Slice tomatoes, Slice mozzarella balls - softer than processed so use a sharp knife. Assemble on a large plate or platter: 1 tomato slice, 1 mozzarella slice shingled / tipped halfway onto tomato slice, 1 basil leaf centered on cheese slice, Repeat all the way around plate and then repeat to center of plate. Chill until served, Drizzle olive oil over all and top with salt and pepper", category:"Appetizer", contributor:"The colors of Italy - red, white & green"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Carrot Cake(loaded)", ingredients:"Cake: 1 box cake mix - either carrot or spice cake(No time for a scratch cake - I could but I don't), 1/2 cup water, 1/2 cup vegetable oil, 4 eggs, 1 can (8 oz.) crushed pineapple in juice / undrained, 1/2 cup shredded carrots, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, 1/2 cup shredded coconut, 1/2 cup raisins. Frosting: 8 oz cream cheese, 4 tbls butter, 2 tbls sour cream, 2 tsp vanilla, 1 lb. powdered sugar", directions:"Cake: Beat cake mix, water, oil, eggs and pineapple with a mixer on low for 30 seconds then on medium for 2 minutes, Blend in carrots, nuts, coconut and raisins, Pour into greased and floured pans - either two 8in round pans or one 9 x 13in pan, Bake at 350 for 30 to 40 minutes depending on the pan size - test for doneness with toothpick in center, Frost with cream cheese frosting and garnish sides of cake with finely ground walnuts. Frosting: Blend approximately 5 minutes until light and fluffy.  Must be refrigerated.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cheese Ball", ingredients:"2 cream cheese - 8 oz each, 1 small pkg dried beef (like for chipped beef), 1/4 cup onion - finely minced, garlic powder to taste, 2 cans squeeze cheese", directions:"Wash and dry off the beef to remove salt, Mince beef, Add all ingredients into a bowl and blend with a mixer. Serve with assorted crackers like a dip or - butter your hands, roll it into a ball, roll it in finely chopped nuts", category:"Appetizer", contributor:"Recipe from Mary and Ernie.  Steve's favorite."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cheesecake Bars", ingredients:"Crust: 1 cup graham cracker crumbs, 3 tbls sugar, 3 tbls butter or margarine - melted. Filling: 4 pkg ( 8oz. Each) Cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, 1 cup sour cream, 4 eggs", directions:"Crust: Mix together and press into bottom only of foil lined 9 x 13 pan, Bake at 325 for 10 minutes. Filling: Beat cream cheese and sugar until well blended, Add vanilla and sour cream - blend well, Add eggs one at a time just until blended, Pour over crust, Bake at 325 for 45 minutes or until center is almost set, drop tbls of pureed fruit over batter and swirl through with a knife blade before baking, add sour cream topping(1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tsp vanilla - spread over baked cheesecake, bake 3 minutes more). Let cool in fridge about 4 hours before slicing", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cheesecake ( No Bake)", ingredients:"8 oz cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 8 oz container Cool Whip, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 graham cracker crust, 1 can Pie filling - cherry, strawberry, blueberry", directions:"Blend cream cheese, sugar and cool whip ( If very stiff add 2 tbls milk ), Put into pie crust, Top with pie filling, Aunt Nora always made her own graham crust, and doubled the filling recipe to make a big 9 x 13 size", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Aunt Nora always made this. This is Steve's favorite")
Recipe.create!(name:"Cheese Filling for baked cookies", ingredients:"1 lb. Bakers cheese ( soft like cream cheese but less moisture ), 5 oz. sugar ( a little more than 1/2 cup ), 1/2 tsp salt, 2 eggs, 3 tbls butter, 1 1/2 tsp vanilla, 2 tbls cake flour, 3 oz milk", directions:"Cream the cheese, sugar and salt, Add eggs, butter and vanilla - blend, Add cake flour, Add enough milk to make spreadable. Good as a filling for Kolaches or thumbprint cookies", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe (formula) from a professional chef in Chicago"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cherry Chocolate Kisses", ingredients:"1 cup butter - softened, 1 cup sifted powdered sugar, 1/8 tsp salt, 2 tsp maraschino cherry liquid, 1/4 tsp almond extract, 2 1/4 cups flour, 1/2 cup chopped maraschino cherries, granulated sugar - to roll balls into, 48 Hershey Kisses - unwrapped", directions:"Cream butter, powdered sugar and salt, Beat in cherry liquid and almond flavoring, Beat in flour and chopped cherries until blended, Shape into 1in balls, Roll in granulated sugar and place on cookie sheet, Flatten to 1/2 inch thickness with a bottom of a glass dipped in sugar, Bake at 325 for 12 to 14 minutes, Remove from oven and immediately press a Hershey Kiss onto each cookie, Cool thoroughly before storing. Hint: I add a little extra cherry liquid. Hint: I use a glass with a pretty cut design on the bottom to press cookies flat. Tastes like Chocolate covered cherries.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cherry Swirl Coffeecake", ingredients:"Cake: 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 cup margarine - softened, 1 1/2 tsp. baking powder, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 tsp almond extract, 1/4 tsp salt, 4 eggs, 3 cups all purpose flour, 1 can (21 oz.) cherry pie filling. Glaze: 1 cup confectioners sugar, 1 to 2 tbls milk", directions:"Cake: Blend sugar, margarine, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract, salt and eggs, Beat for three minutes on high speed, Stir in flour, Spread 2/3 of the mixture in a well greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan, Spread pie filling over batter, Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls - scattering over top of pie filling, Spread slightly, Bake at 350 for 45 minutes until light brown, While warm - drizzle with glaze, Cool completely and cut into bars. Glaze: Blend and drizzle", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from Jamie"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Chicken & Dumplings(large batch - cut recipe in half for smaller batch)", ingredients:"2 whole chickens, 4 quarts water, 2 tbls. Chicken base or 2 to 3 boullion cubes, 4 cups all purpose flour, 2 cups self-rising flour - (if you don't have this then use all purpose and add 2 tbls. baking powder), 4 eggs, 1/2 cup vegetable oil, 1 tsp. salt, pepper (if desired), 2 cups canned chicken broth", directions:"Clean the chickens thoroughly, Place in a large pot and cover with the water, Bring to a boil and then lower temperature to medium, Cook for 45 minutes, Remove chicken from broth so that it can get cool enough to remove from the bone, Stir boullion into hot broth, While the chicken is cooking mix together all other ingredients in a large bowl, Add half of the canned chicken broth at first and then add more as needed until you have a soft dough, Sprinkle additional flour on the counter or table and roll out 1/4th of the dough at a time, Hint:  It took me a lot of years to learn that it has to be rolled very, very thin (read the paper through it thin), Cut into 1 inch squares and dust with additional flour before lifting them up, Bring the pot of broth back up to a slow boil, Drop a few dumplings at a time into the broth and stir gently, Repeat with remaining dough - you may not need all of it (Mom says to freeze the extra on cookie sheets), After all dumplings have been added - lower the flame to simmer, Dumplings will sink below the broth when they are cooked - don't over stir them, Add the boned chicken in with the dumplings (you can also add a little milk if you want a creamier gravy), Simmer a few minutes more - turn off burner - broth will thicken as it cools", category:"", contributor:"Recipe from Mom - Janet Healy"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Chicken Salad with Grapes", ingredients:"1 whole chicken, 1 cup red seedless grapes, 1 tbl Marsala wine (dry red wine), 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 2 tbls milk, salt & pepper to taste, walnuts - optional, celery - optional", directions:"Boil chicken until tender, remove from pan and let cool - remove chicken from bone and place in a mixing bowl, Cut each grape in half and add to bowl with chicken, In another small bowl mix the wine, mayo, milk, salt & pepper - pour over the chicken and grapes then fold gently, Chill until served ~ good with assorted crackers or as a sandwich", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Recipe from Kelly.  Her sister-in-law sometimes adds walnuts or celery for extra crunch and flavor."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cauliflower Salad", ingredients:"1 head of cauliflower - cut into bite size florettes, 8 oz shredded cheddar cheese, 4 strips of bacon - fried crisp and then crumbled, 1/2 cup mayo, 2 tbls milk, 1 tbl sugar", directions:"Blend mayo, milk and sugar then pour over cauliflower, cheese and bacon - chill for several hours", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"surprise---bonus recipe from Kelly"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Cole Slaw (loaded)", ingredients:"3 to 4 cups shredded cabbage, 1 carrot shredded, 1 cucumber chopped, 1 tomato chopped (or use cherry/grape tomatoes cut in half), 3 tbls mayonnaise, 2 tbls Italian dressing, salt & pepper to taste", directions:"combine all and chill, add more mayo or dressing as needed. Hint:  Mom says to not shred the cabbage too close to the core or the salad will be bitter. Hint 2: Save the core for oldest son and give him a salt shaker, too.", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"This has always been Matthew's favorite way to have cole slaw. "),
Recipe.create!(name:"Corn Pudding", ingredients:"2 cans cream style corn, 1 stick of butter, 4 eggs, 2 tbls flour, 1/2 cup sugar (may use a little less if desired), 1 cup milk", directions:"Blend together and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake in a slow oven - 250 degrees for about 1 hour until golden brown(It will puff up like a custard and the slow oven will keep it from burning while allowing the eggs to cook)", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"From my friend that sends me dinner plates full enough for several meals when my work load is busy and I don't take time to slow down.  This is usually on there and it is delicious."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Deviled Eggs", ingredients:"6 hard boiled eggs ( peeled ), 1/2 tsp yellow mustard, 1 tsp sweet pickle juice, 1 tbls mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste, paprika for garnish only", directions:"cut eggs in half lengthwise and pop out yolks into a bowl, mash yolks with a fork until very fine, add mustard, sweet pickle juice, mayo, salt and pepper - mix well, to fill egg halves you can just spoon the filling in or put filling in a ziplock bag, snip the corner and fill eggs or you can use a disposable decorator bag and tip to make them fancier, lightly sprinkle with paprika for decoration, store in refrigerator. Hint:  Mom leaves the egg white halves on paper towels in the container in the the fridge then she removes the paper towels and fills them just before serving this prevents the eggs and filling from becoming runny (wet)", category:"Side Dish", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Divinity  (Seafoam candy)", ingredients:"2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup Karo syrup, 1/2 cup water, 1/2 tsp salt, 2 egg whites, 1 tsp vanilla", directions:"Heat sugar, Karo syrup, water and salt to boiling over medium heat stirring frequently, Boil to hard ball stage(test in bowl of ice water - drizzle hot mixture into ice water and mixture should turn into hard crackles), do not allow to burn or brown. In a separate bowl - whip egg whites until stiff, Add vanilla, Pour hot mixture into egg whites while beating with paddle attachment or heavy wooden spoon, Pour in a very slow steady stream, Beat until cooled enough to hold shape, Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper, Decorate with red or green glazed cherry halves or nut halves. Variations - use other extracts instead of vanilla (orange, lemon, cherry, peppermint)tint with food coloring to make different holiday colors, add finely ground nuts during combining stage and black walnut extract, add miniature chocolate chips when almost cold enough to shape", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Eclairs", ingredients:"1 cup water, 1/2 cup shortening, 1 cup flour, 4 eggs", directions:"Bring water and shortening to a rolling boil, Stir in flour and mix until it forms a ball - remove from heat, Stir to cool down (cooler than body temperature), Beat in eggs one at a time- Beat until smooth, Shape into logs for eclairs  or shape into  rounds for crème puffs, Bake at 400 for 45-50 minutes till puffed and golden brown, Allow to cool slowly, Fill eclairs with vanilla pudding and frost with fudge frosting, Fill crème puffs with whipped crème and dust with powdered sugar. Makes approximately 12", category:"", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Egg Salad", ingredients:"6 hard boiled eggs ( peeled ), 1/2 cup finely minced celery, 2 tbls pickle relish ( or finely minced sweet pickles if you want to do all of that work ), 1 tsp yellow mustard, 2 tbls mayonnaise, salt & pepper to taste", directions:"dice eggs or just mince with a fork, add all other ingredients and blend well, add more mayo if needed, some people like a little minced onion in their egg salad - your option", category:"Side Dish", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Eggs Benedict", ingredients:"1 pkg Hollandaisse sauce mix (or two if Steve and Ashes are around), 8 slices of canadian bacon (or use thick sliced ham), 8 eggs - to be poached but I've also learned that fried sunny side up is okay, too, 4 english muffins - split into 8 halves, butter (or margarine if you are like Mary and can't stand butter - she was adopted, I think)", directions:"Timing is everything here. Toast the english muffins and butter them as they come out of the toaster, Heat the canadian bacon (or ham) in a medium skillet until warm, Make the hollandaisse sauce according to package directions and keep warm over a pot or bowl of hot water, In a large skillet, heat about 2 inches of water to a slow boil and add 1 capful of vinegar, the vinegar keeps the poached eggs from spreading out in the pan, Cook 4 eggs at a time - dropping one at a time into the water - do not overcook or yolks will get hard, Remove from water with a slotted spoon or utensil, Cook next 4 eggs while you assemble the first 4 - see below. Assemble: One plate, two buttered muffin halves, Canadian bacon or ham on each muffin half, one egg on to of each ham/muffin combo, ladel sauce over all, salt and pepper to taste, Serve with hash browns if desired.", category:"Breakfast", contributor:"I got up the courage to finally try this at a restaurant about 10 years ago and then I learned to make it. Steve and Ashley have it more often than most of us - it is their favorite.  (with extra sauce of course)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fried Chicken", ingredients:"1 whole frying chicken cut up (see below) (or a package of already cut-up chicken pieces) - washed thoroughly, 2 cups buttermilk, salt and pepper to taste. In a bowl - cover chicken with buttermilk, salt and pepper / cover bowl and refrigerate overnight. Batter: 2 cups self-rising flour (or regular with 1/2 tsp each baking powder and baking soda), 1 tsp salt, 1 tsp pepper, 1 tsp paprika, 1 doubled paper bag (traditional method) or gallon size ziplock bag", directions:"Drain chicken, Put flour and seasonings into the bag, Drop in chicken a couple of pieces at a time and shake bag to coat (please, close the bag first), Heat about 2 inches of vegetable oil (Crisco or Crisco oil is best) in a deep frying pan, A cast iron skillet is best but any skillet will do, Place coated chicken gently into hot oil, Fry for 10 minutes making sure the heat isn't so high that you burn everything, Turn over all chicken pieces, Fry for 10 minutes more, Fry to a golden brown on each side, Remove chicken and drain on paper towels.", category:"Dinner", contributor:"This is as close as I can come to a family friend's father's recipe because the recipe is a well guarded secret. Hmmmmm………………. Hint:  Cutting a whole chicken > cut off 2 wings at joint, cut off 2 whole legs at joint and then cut legs in two where the thigh and drumstick meets giving you 4 pieces, feel for the front edge of the breast bone and cut straight down then angle out to remove the wishbone (with chicken on it),  Cut below the breast meat where it meets the back - all the way through, end to end - to get one whole breast portion.  This can be split down the middle to get 2 breast halves if desired.  8 or 9 pieces total. Use the back, neck and giblets to flavor a soup broth.  Waste not / want not."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fried Green Tomatoes", ingredients:"3 large light green (almost ready to turn) tomatoes (Mom likes to use 'pink' tomatoes), 1 egg, 2 tbls milk or water, 1/2  cup corn meal, 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper, vegetable oil or bacon grease - enough for 1/2 inch in large frying pan", directions:"Remove core of tomatoes, Slice tomatoes about 1/2 inch thick, In a bowl - beat egg and 2 tbls milk or water just until blended, In another bowl stir corn meal, flour, salt and pepper together, Now dip each tomato slice in the egg mixture and then dredge in the corn meal mixture, Gently place into the oil that has been heated over a medium temperature, Fry until golden brown about 3 minutes on each side, Drain on paper towel", category:"Side Dish", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fruit Salad", ingredients:"1/2 watermelon, 1 small cantaloupe, 1 small honeydew melon, 1 pineapple, 1 container strawberries, 1 container blueberries, 4 Kiwi - peeled, 1/2 cup honey or light corn syrup", directions:"Wash all fruit before starting.  Important!, Cube or melonball the melons - place in large bowl, Cube the pineapple - add to bowl, Remove stems from the strawberries, cut in half - add to bowl, Add blueberries, Cube Kiwi - add to bowl, Pour honey or corn syrup over all and mix gently, Chill 1 hour and mix again before serving", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"A refreshing addition to any gathering where food is center stage.  Make it fancy using a melonballer or just cut it all into medium sized cubes."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fudge - Chocolate", ingredients:"3 cups sugar, 3/4 cup butter (1 1/2 sticks), 1 small can (5 oz) evaporated milk (about 2/3 cup), 12 oz. chocolate squares or 12 oz bag of chocolate chips, 1 - 7 oz jar Marshmallow crème, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 cup coarsely chopped walnuts", directions:"In a 3 qt saucepan - heat sugar, butter and evaporated milk over medium heat to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly, boil for at least 4 minutes to soft ball stage, remove from heat, Stir in chocolate pieces and marshmallow crème until melted, Stir in vanilla and chopped walnuts, Spread immediately in a foil lined 9 inch pan, I usually use a larger pan or two smaller ones for a more shallow layer, Let cool completely then cut into squares, No foil? - just butter the pan or plate really well", category:"Dessert", contributor:"You can also make a Peanut Butter fudge using peanut butter chips and 1 cup peanut butter. I have made a very thin layer of each in the same pan for a two tone fudge - cut when cool. You can also fold in rainbow colored marshmallows at the very last minute for a holiday fudge. Try adding oatmeal and dropping by spoonfuls for no-bake cookies. Try adding coconut or raisins or almonds or peanuts"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fudge Frosting", ingredients:"1 cup sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, 1/4 cup butter (1 stick), 1/2 cup milk, 2 tbls light corn syrup, dash of salt, 2 cups powdered sugar, 1 tsp vanilla", directions:"Combine sugar and cocoa in a 2 quart saucepan, add butter, milk, corn syrup and salt, Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes), Continue boiling, stirring occasionally for 6 more minutes, Cool 1 hour, Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Makes approx. 1 and 3/4 cups"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Fudge (Old Fashioned Sugary Type)", ingredients:"12 oz. evaporated milk ( 1 can ), 2/3 cup cocoa, 3 cups sugar, 1/4 tsp salt, 1/4 cup butter ( 1/2 a stick ), 1 tsp vanilla", directions:"Combine cocoa, sugar and salt, Add evaporated milk, Bring to boil over high heat then lower to medium heat, Continue to boil without stirring until softball stage - about 4 minutes, Remove from heat, Add butter and vanilla, Beat until cooled, Pour into buttered pan or buttered plates. Peanut Butter ( Old Fashioned Sugary Type). Eliminate cocoa, Add 1 cup peanut butter in last step when you add the butter and vanilla. Nuts can be added to either type if desired", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"German Chocolate Frosting", ingredients:"1 cup evaporated milk, 1 cup sugar, 3 egg yolks - slightly beaten, 1/2 cup butter or margarine, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 1/3 cups coconut, 1 cup chopped pecans", directions:"Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in saucepan, Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened - about 12 minutes, Remove from heat, Add coconut and nuts, Cool until spreading consistency. I usually make either a German Chocolate cake which is a lighter chocolate or Devils Food which is darker I make two 8in layers - cool them down and then split them to make four thin layers Put filling between each layer and on top Double the recipe if you like more frosting than cake like I do.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Gingerbread House", ingredients:"1 cup unsalted butter (2 sticks), 1 1/2 cups packed brown sugar, 2 eggs, 1 cup dark molasses ( not blackstrap ), 1 tsp vanilla, 6 1/4 cups cake flour, 4 tsp ground ginger, 2 tsp cinnamon, 1 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp ground cloves, 1/2 tsp salt, Gingerbread house templates - recipe follows, Assorted candies for decorating - make them colorful - frosted shredded mini bites for roof", directions:"Cream the butter until smooth, add sugar and blend until fluffy, add eggs one at a time and blend, add molasses and vanilla, mix, Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, cloves and salt.  Blend into mixture a little at a time, Shape into a disc, wrap and chill 1 to 2 hours, Roll out half of dough on a lightly floured surface to a 1/4 inch thick, Use templates to cut out house shapes - hint>lay dough on baking sheet and cut out there so it won't stretch, Bake at 350 for 10 to 15 minutes until stiff and toasty. Use royal icing to 'glue' walls together-dry 30 minutes-frost pieces and apply candies quickly-pipe on snow drifts", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Templates: Use brown paper bags or parchment paper to cut out templates, You will need to make 7 templates by drawing out the dimensions on the paper and then cutting them out, 2 front and rear walls - 5 inches high by 8 inches long, cut out two windows from each wall and one 2 1/2 " by 1 1/2" door from one wall, 2 side walls shaped like a house (triangle on a square) 5 inches high by 6 inches long, with a triangle 7 inches high on top (cut all in one piece), cut a window out of each side wall, 2 overhanging roof pieces - 4 1/2 inches wide by 9 inches long, 1 door - 2 1/2 inches high by 1 1/2 inches wide."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Ham", ingredients:"choose your ham - shank, butt, whole or canned, score with knife in crisscross pattern (ends up looking like diamond shapes), stud with whole cloves - one in each diamond shape, place in roasting pan, pour one 12 ounce can of 7-up into the pan, cover, ", directions:"Bake at 350 for 15 minutes per pound of ham, Results in a very tender, juicy ham, Cooking bag can be used also", category:"Dinner", contributor:"as recommended by a Chef in Chicago"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Hard Candy", ingredients:"3 3/4 cups sugar, 1 1/2 cups light Karo syrup, 1 cup water, 1 tsp Lorann flavoring oil ( see list below ), Several drops of food coloring to match flavor, Powdered sugar for dusting. Flavors: Anise, Apricot, Banana Crème, Blackberry, Black Walnut, Butter, Butter Rum, Butterscotch, Cherry, Chocolate, Cinnamon, Clove, Coconut, Grape, Horehound, Lemon, Licorice, Lime, Maple, Nutmeg, Orange, Peppermint, Pineapple, Plum, Raspberry, Rootbeer, Sassafras, Spearmint, Strawberry, Vanilla Butternut, Watermelon, Wintergreen", directions:"In a large saucepan mix sugar, syrup and water, Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves, Bring to a boil without stirring until it reaches 310 degrees or hard ball stage, Remove from heat, After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and food coloring, Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet, Cool - then break into pieces - store in an airtight container, We used to dust ours with powdered sugar to keep it from being sticky (but it didn't last long)", category:"Dessert", contributor:"One of Patrick's favorites. Lorann Oils, Inc. Lansing, Michigan"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Hashbrown Casserole", ingredients:"1 large hashbrown casserole, 1 can of cream of chicken soup, 8 oz. sour cream, 1 stick butter - softened, 2 cups of shredded cheddar cheese, corn flakes ( as many as you feel like putting on)", directions:"mix all ingredients except the corn flakes, bake at 350 for about 35 minutes, then top with corn flakes, bake for approximately 15 to 25 minutes more until corn flakes are golden brown, be careful not to burn it, Ashley always puts extra cheese in the mix and extra cornflakes on top", category:"", contributor:"Recipe from Ashley"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Hawaiian Salad ( five cup salad)", ingredients:"1 cup mandarin orange slices (drained), 1 cup pineapple chunks (drained), 1 cup sour cream, 1 cup coconut, 1 cup miniature marshmallows, Maraschino cherries - chopped ( optional for color)", directions:"Stir all together - chill, Best made day in advance so marshmallows melt down somewhat, Can be made with multicolored mini marshmallows, also. Keep refrigerated", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Hints (heard, learned & read )", ingredients:"", directions:"To make cutting corn off of the cob easier, use a bundt pan.  Stand the ear of corn in the center hole and as you slice down the kernels will fall into the ring of the pan. Freeze any flavor of fruit yogurt right in its original cup(wide top) for 1 hour - then remove lid and insert a popsicle stick in the center - return to freezer for 6 hours - pop it out of the cup and enjoy. To keep water in a pot of pasta from boiling over - rub oil around the top inner edge of the pan. Most recipes that only specify eggs as an ingredient mean large eggs not medium or jumbo. You can soak chicken in buttermilk for a couple of hours or overnight to tenderize and flavor the meat. You can soak fish in buttermilk for a couple of hours or overnight to tone down the 'fishy' odor and taste. When baking brownies add 1/4 cup Hershey Special Dark Syrup to the batter, They are done when a toothpick comes out clean when tested 2 inches in from the edge, The center will finish baking after you remove it from the oven. Use shiny pans for baking cookies - not the dark coated kind. Use club soda instead of water or milk in pancake mix to get a lighter, fluffy pancake. Always wash fruit before cutting into it - melons, too.  Melons can hold salmonella bacteria on the rind that will be dragged into the fruit when you cut them.  Scrub them first. If it grows below the ground start the cooking in cold water. If it grows above the ground start the cooking in boiling water. Easy meal - 1 large can chicken broth, 1 lb. spaghetti, 1 pkg frozen Italian veggies, 1/2 stick butter, Put in large pot, cook until broth is absorbed, salt and pepper to taste Add diced chicken if desired", category:"Hints", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Hye Rollers", ingredients:"1 pkg flat bread (available at most grocery stores) or large flour tortillas, 1 pkg cream cheese softened, Ham, turkey or roast beef from the deli sliced very thin, American cheese, Swiss cheese and cheddar cheese - sliced thin, Lettuce - shredded very fine, Tomatoes - sliced very thin", directions:"Spread cream cheese very thin over 3/4 of one flat bread or tortilla, Spread lettuce over cream cheese layer, Place three tomato slices in a row- in the center- covering side to side, Lay deli meat in a single thin layer to cover the entire lettuce area, Lay 2 slices of deli cheese over deli meat layer, Starting at covered end - roll up tightly to other end - ingredients will push forward somewhat to cover all, Chill, Slice into 1 or 1-1/2in sections to make pinwheels and lay flat on platter", category:"Lunch", contributor:"Pinwheel sandwiches good for picnics or event showers. Do not layer tomatoes next to cheese because the tomato acid will make the cheese runny, Make any combinations of meat and cheese desired, You can also make these with a spinach dip or chicken salad and roll tiny pinwheels for appetizers"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Italian Cookies - Easy", ingredients:"Cookies: 1 cup butter, 1 cup sugar, 4 tsp baking powder, 2 eggs, 1 tbl vanilla, 4 cups flour (use 3 and a half cups then add more if too sticky). Glaze: 2 cups powdered sugar, 2 tbls milk, 1 tsp flavoring ( anise, orange, lemon or vanilla )", directions:"Blend flour and baking powder - set aside, Cream butter and sugar, Beat in eggs and vanilla, Beat in flour mixture just until blended, Roll into 1in balls then roll balls into 4 inch rope and shape as an 'S' (or press down ball with sugar dipped glass), Place on ungreased cookie sheets, Bake at 350 for 8 to 10 minutes, Glaze cookies while still warm, garnish with colored crystal sugar or fruit zest if desired", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Jambalaya (made with smoked sausage)", ingredients:"2 - 16oz pkgs smoked sausage - sliced into semi thin rounds, 3 large green peppers - cut into strips or large chunks, 2 large onions - chopped, 1 large can stewed tomatoes or 6 large fresh tomatoes, 1 tbl olive oil", directions:"Lightly brown smoked sausage in olive oil, Add green pepper and onion - lower heat - cover and let simmer until soft, Add tomatoes and cook down but not dried out, Serve over rice or noodles", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Christopher's favorite"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Kris Kringles", ingredients:"1/2 cup butter, softened, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 beaten egg yolk, 1 tsp grated lemon peel, 1 tbl grated orange peel, 1 tsp lemon juice, 1 cup sifted flour, 1 slightly beaten egg white, dash of salt, 2/3 cup finely chopped walnuts or pecans, Candied cherry halves for tops - need approx. 26 halves", directions:"Cream butter and sugar.  Add egg yolk and lemon juice, lemon and orange peel, Add flour and salt just until blended.  Chill 1 hour, Form into small 1in balls, Dip into beaten egg white and roll lightly into chopped nuts, Place on a greased cookie sheet, Press half a candied cherry in center of each, Bake at 325 for approximately 20 minutes", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Kolaches (pronounced ca-lotch-kees)", ingredients:"1 lb. butter (4 sticks), 1/2 cup sugar, 2 egg yolks (save whites for Schaum cookies or divinity), 1/2 pint sour cream, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 4 to 5 cups flour (I use 4 because a lot will get rolled into the dough later), 1/2 tsp vanilla, Assorted fruit or almond pastry fillings (Solo or Bohemian Kitchen brands), (Pineapple, Apricot, Raspberry, Cherry, Strawberry and Almond are good), If you use jelly make it a good quality preserves type or it will boil out, Powdered sugar for dusting", directions:"Cream butter and sugar, Add egg yolks, Add vanilla, Add flour & soda alternating with sour cream, Divide into 3 or 4 flattened discs, Wrap in plastic and chill 1 hour, Roll out a disc to 1/8 inch thin, Cut into 2in x 2in squares, Put 1/2 tsp filling on each square, Fold one corner over to the center, Fold opposite corner over to the center and press, or you can fold all four corners in to be able to tell different fillings for different shapes, Bake at 400 for approximately 10 minutes or until slightly browned - Dust with powdered sugar while still warm", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Lasagna", ingredients:"Mom's: 8 cups of pasta sauce (or two 32oz jars) (if you use jar sauce add 1 or 2 lbs. cooked ground beef), 1 pkg lasagna noodles, 1 pkg (small) frozen peas, 2 lbs shredded mozzarella (what can I say - we liked the cheese). Traditional: Same as above except eliminate peas. Ricotta Cheese Filling: 1 container ricotta cheese - drained for 1 hour in a mesh colander or cheesecloth, 2 eggs, 1 tbl chopped parsley, salt and pepper to taste, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese.", directions:"Mom's: Cook lasagna noodles until al dente (almost soft), Put a thin layer of sauce in the bottom of a deep baking pan or roaster, Put a layer of noodles laid side by side across the pan over the sauce, Put a layer of shredded cheese, Put a sprinkling of peas over the cheese, Repeat layers but turn noodle direction on every other layer (one layer long way, one layer short way), Final layer should be cheese, Mom pours a little water down in around the edges, Bake at 350 for 1 hour. Traditional: Layer in the center should be ricotta cheese filling about 1 inch thick, Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until center is melted (it should no longer look like cottage cheese). Ricotta Cheese Filling: Blend well and spoon into center layer of lasagna assembly, Can also be used for manicotti filling and stuffed jumbo shells. Alfredo style: Cook noodles al dente, cool in cold water, pat dry, spread each noodle with a thin layer of ricotta filling, Roll up pinwheel style and lay in a buttered casserole dish.  Pour 1 jar Alfredo sauce over rolls, Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until filling is melted", category:"Dinner", contributor:"I will include several variations starting with the way Mom always made it for us.  You can either use the 'cook all day' homemade spaghetti sauce or your favorite brand of sauce in a jar. Traditional lasagna has a thick ricotta cheese layer in it - recipe is below."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Lemon Chicken Bow Tie", ingredients:"1 1/2 lbs. boneless, skinless chicken breast, 2 tbls olive oil (use vegetable oil if you don't have olive oil), 1/2 cup onion - minced, 1 bottle of Lemon Pepper marinade (my friend uses Lawry's brand 12 oz. bottle), 1 cup sliced mushrooms - optional, 1 cup frozen peas, 1 lb. Bow Tie pasta", directions:"Cut chicken into small strips or nuggets, Add enough oil to coat the bottom of a large frying pan, Cook chicken and onion over medium heat  until chicken is no longer pink on the outside, Pour in the lemon pepper marinade - the whole bottle, Add the mushrooms and peas, Simmer for approximately 20 minutes, Meanwhile cook the bow tie pasta and drain, Combine the chicken mixture with the pasta and serve hot, Salt and pepper to taste, Serve as a meal with some other veggies like carrots, corn, etc.", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Recipe from a friend of the family."),
Recipe.create!(name:"M & M Cookies", ingredients:"1 cup butter or margarine, 1/2 cup granulated sugar, 1/2 cup firmly packed light brown sugar, 1 large egg, 1 tsp vanilla, 2 cups all purpose flour, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1/8 tsp salt, 1 - 12 oz package Mini M&M's = 1 3/4 cups, 3/4 cup chopped nuts (optional)", directions:"cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy, beat in egg and vanilla, in another bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt, blend into creamed mixture, Stir in M&M's and nuts, Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls - 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet, Bake at 350 for 10 to 13 minutes or until edges are lightly browned and centers are still soft, Makes about 3 dozen 3in cookies, Works with regular size M&M's too", category:"", contributor:"Recipe off of the package of mini M&M's - in case they ever stop printing it"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Mexican Wedding Cookies", ingredients:"2 cups Butter, 1 cup powdered sugar, 4 cups flour, 1 tsp salt, 2 tsp vanilla, 2 cups finely ground pecans", directions:"Cream butter and powdered sugar, Add remaining ingredients, Chill 1 hour, Roll into 1in balls, Bake at 375 for approximately 12 minutes, Dust with powdered sugar while still hot from oven, Recipe can be cut in half for smaller batch", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Nacho Layered Dip", ingredients:"2 cream cheese 8 oz size - softened, 1 packet taco mix, 1 can refried beans - optional, 1 lb. ground beef - browned and crumbled - seasoned with salt and pepper, 1/2 jar salsa - any kind, 1 1/2 cups shredded / chopped lettuce, 1 cups diced tomatoes, 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese, 1/2 can black olives - sliced, 1/2 cup chopped green onion, Large bag of tortilla chips", directions:"Mix taco powder mix with cream cheese, On a large platter: Spread cream cheese mixture over entire platter, Spread refried beans over cream cheese, Spread ground beef over refried beans, Spread salsa over ground beef, Continue layering with all other ingredients, Chill until served", category:"Appitizer", contributor:"Recipe from Matthew.  He makes it for every gathering and if you are late you don't get any !!!  "),
Recipe.create!(name:"New England Boiled Dinner", ingredients:"4 lb Corned Beef, 2 lbs. Carrots, 3 lbs. new potatoes ( baby size ), 1 large head cabbage, Pickling spice, Cheese cloth, salt & pepper", directions:"In large stock pot or dutch oven: peel carrots and cut into 2in chunks, wash potatoes and only peel one strip all the way around, leaving red peel on ends, cut cabbage into wedges, cut square of cheesecloth - put 2 tbls pickling spice in center - gather up edges - tie off with thread, Hint: no cheesecloth just add the spices to the pot, Put corned beef on top of veggies, Salt & pepper to taste, Bring to boil and then lower heat to low/medium for 2 hours, Serve with Rye bread or Irish Soda bread Hint: Years ago someone told me to use the juice from Claussen pickles - spices and all - I did and it was fine, too.", category:"Dinner", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"No-Bake Cookies", ingredients:"4 cups sugar, 1 cup evaporated milk, 1/2 cup margarine or butter, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1/2 tsp salt, 6 cups oatmeal", directions:"In large pan - bring first 5 ingredients to a boil over medium heat, Boil, stirring constantly for 4 minutes (softball stage), Remove from heat, Stir in oatmeal and beat until cooled down, Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or parchment paper", category:"Dessert", contributor:"(Hide from brother and oldest son or you won't get any)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Nut Cups - Recipe from Solo filling label (good )", ingredients:"2 - 3 oz pkgs cream cheese, 1 cup butter or margarine, 2 cups flour, 2 eggs, 1 cup brown sugar, 1 can Solo Apricot Filling, 1 cup chopped nuts", directions:"Blend cream cheese and margarine or butter into flour using a pastry blender, Form into 48 - 1in balls, Line miniature muffin pans with balls and indent each to make crust, For filling combine eggs, brown sugar, apricot filling and nuts, Spoon into individual crusts, Bake at 350 for 20 minutes - Cool in pans, Hint: Cut 6oz off an 8oz bar of cream cheese and use the other 2oz for filling(blend with egg, sugar, 1/2 tsp vanilla and 1 tsp flour), Splenda can be substituted for sugar free fillings", category:"Dessert", contributor:"The base dough is sugar free so fillings can also be made using Simply Fruit Preserves and / or cream cheese"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Omega Special", ingredients:"1 box Devil's Food cake mix, 1 pkg Devil's Food instant pudding, 1 egg, 1 frozen cheesecake (Sara Lee, Eli's or any brand of whole cheesecake)(keep it frozen), 2 to 3 cans of fudge frosting (or homemade)", directions:"Make cake according to package directions except add in the pudding mix and extra egg, Bake according to directions - turn out on cooling racks, When cake is cool - split the two layers horizontally - now you have four layers. Assembly: thin cake layer, thin fudge frosting, thin cake layer, thin fudge frosting, frozen cheesecake (scrape off the graham bottom crust if you want to), thin fudge frosting, thin cake layer, thin fudge frosting, thin cake layer, Now frost the entire cake - sides and top, Decorate with chocolate dipped strawberries if desired, Cake will be about 6 inches tall, You could also make it using one layer - split - cake, fudge, cheesecake, fudge, cake and then frost all, You could substitute a strawberry cheesecake instead of plain", category:"Dessert", contributor:"This is my copy of a very delicious cake dessert at a local restaurant. You could make it all from scratch if you want to - you could but I don't."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Oven Baked Applebutter", ingredients:"3 qts applesauce ( or a 6 3/4 pound restaurant size can ), 3 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 tsp allspice, 1/4 tsp ground nutmeg, 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup light brown sugar, 1/4 cup dark brown sugar", directions:"Pre-heat oven to 275, Mix all ingredients in a large, heavy bottomed (oven safe) pot, Stir until you're sure all sugars are dissolved, I do this stirring on the stove top with some heat on to give the sauce a warm head-start, Bake the sauce mixture, uncovered, at 275 for 8 hours, At this temperature no stirring is needed during the baking cycle, I often bake it overnight and the house sure smells delicious when I get up, Turn off the oven and let the applebutter take advantage of the residual heat while you have your morning coffee, Your 12 cups of applesauce will have reduced to about 9 cups of applebutter, It will reduce in volume a little bit more as it cools and of course become a little bit thicker, Can it if you want but this applebutter freezes well with no loss of flavor", category:"", contributor:"recipe from cajunclarkssweetandsassy.com ( like Mamaw used to make) Let your conscience be your guide as you decide to tell the relatives whether you actually peeled, cored and processed all those apples"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pasta Salad", ingredients:"1 lb. pkg. Rotini ( regular or tri-colored)  any hearty shaped pasta will do, 1 cup each (chopped, diced, sliced how ever you like it): celery, cucumber, broccoli, carrots, tomatoes, artichoke hearts, olives - black, 1 large bottle Newman's Own original Italian dressing ( there is no sugar or corn syrup in this one ), Options ( other items that can be added if desired ): green olives, sliced water chestnuts, pickled baby corn, red onion, parmesan cheese, green, red, yellow or orange pepper, cauliflower, yellow squash, zucchini squash, mushrooms, Ranch dressing, Caesar dressing", directions:"Cook pasta to al dente ( almost completely soft but not quite ), Rinse in cold water and drain, add all other ingredients including dressing, add salt & pepper to taste", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"Christopher's favorite"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Peach Cobbler (double crust)", ingredients:"3 cans peach filling, 1/2 tsp almond extract, 1 tsp cinnamon", directions:"Stir until blended - fill bottom crust, See pie crust recipe, Enough to fill a 10 x 15 pan (or 9 x 13 for thicker cobbler), Before putting top crust on - dot with butter randomly over fruit, With pointed knife dot a design into top crust (for design and for venting purposes), Brush top with evaporated milk and sprinkle with sugar if desired, Bake at 350 for approximately 1 hour", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Hint:  My grandmother used to tuck tiny pieces of dough between fruit to puff up like dumplings within the cobbler."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Peanut Butter Cookies (Ma's)", ingredients:"1 cup crisco, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 cup peanut butter, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup brown sugar, 2 eggs, 1 tbl milk, 2 cups flour, 1/2 tsp soda", directions:"Cream crisco, salt & peanut butter, Add both sugars and cream well, Add eggs and milk, Blend in flour and soda just until mixed, Roll into 1in balls, Dip fork in water and press down top of cookie to flatten, then turn fork 1/4 turn and press again to make criss-cross marks, Bake at 325 for 15 to 20 minutes  makes 10 to 12 dozen, Recipe can be cut in half", category:"Dessert", contributor:"(recipe from Matt, Chris and Steve's grandma)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Peanut Butter Kiss Cookies", ingredients:"1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup packed brown sugar, 1/2 cup butter, 1/2 cup peanut butter ( I use smooth, Mary uses crunchy) (Mary also says to use only Jif brand), 2 tbls milk, 1 egg, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 3/4 cup flour, 1 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp salt, granulated sugar to roll dough balls into, Hershey Kisses - un-wrapped", directions:"Blend sugars and butter until creamy, Add peanut butter, milk, egg and vanilla - blend well, In a separate bowl blend flour, soda and salt then add to first bowl - just until blended - not too long, Roll into balls - 3/4 to 1 inch size, Roll balls in granulated sugar, Bake at 375 for approximately 8 minutes, Press a Hershey Kiss into each cookie as soon as you remove the pan from the oven - the cookie will crackle at the edges, Cool completely before packing for storage or the heat will make the chocolate kiss turn white/gray", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Mary's"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Paula's Pecan Pie", ingredients:"3 eggs (an extra won't hurt), 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup white Karo Syrup  --- (or 1/2 cup white and 1/2 cup dark Karo syrup), 1/8 tsp salt, 1 tsp vanilla, 1 cup pecans", directions:"Blend first five ingredients, Spread pecan halves in bottom of unbaked deep dish pie shell, Pour filling over pecans - gently, Bake at 350 for 1 hour, Pecans will rise to the top", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Paula is Mary's sister-in-law and graciously shared her recipe with us.  I only use her crust recipe now."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pepper Steak", ingredients:"1 lb lean roundsteak ( 1/2 inch thick ), 1 tbl paprika, 2 tbls margarine or butter, 2 cloves garlic - crushed, 1 1/2 cups beef broth, 1 cup sliced green onions - include tops, 2 green peppers - cut into strips, 2 tbls corn starch, 1/4 cup water, 1/4 cup soy sauce, 2 large tomatoes cut into eighths", directions:"Pound steak to 1/4in thick, Cut into 1/4in strips, Sprinkle with paprika and set aside while preparing other ingredients, In a large skillet, brown the meat in butter, Add garlic and broth, Cover and simmer 30 minutes, Add onions and green peppers - cook 5 minutes more, Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce, Stir into meat mixture, Cook stirring until clear and thickened - about 2 minutes, Add tomatoes and stir gently, Serve over beds of rice, Serves 6 ( unless you have teen-age boys  )", category:"Dinner", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Paula's Pie Crust", ingredients:"4 cups flour, 1 tbl baking powder, 1 1/2 tsp salt, 1 1/2 cups lard or 1 3/4 cups Crisco (lard is best), 1 egg, 2 tbls vinegar, 1/2 cup milk", directions:"Mix First Three Thoroughly, Add lard or Crisco and mix until crumbly, Mix wet ingredients in a separate bowl, add to flour/lard mixture, Divide dough into two flattened discs and chill for one hour, Roll out to 1/8in - 1/4in thickness, Enough for a large full crust cobbler or two deep dish pies with lattice tops or one full crust pie and one bottom crust for cream pie or pecan pie, Bake at 350 - 375 for 45 minutes to an hour, Sprinkle sugar on top of fruit pies, DO NOT - try to double the recipe, it loses it's formula balance (been there ~ done that, what a mess)", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Paula"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pineapple Up-side Down Cake", ingredients:"1/3 cup butter ( about 5 1/2 tbls ), 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 can sliced pineapple drained ( have also made with crushed pineapple ), 1 1/3 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, 2 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/3 cup shortening, 2/3 cup milk, 1 tsp vanilla, 1/2 tsp lemon extract, 1 egg", directions:"Use a 9in deep cake pan or double recipe for a 9 x 13, Melt butter in cake pan, Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over entire pan, Arrange pineapple slices ( optional - place Maraschino cherry in each ring ), Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl, Add shortening, milk and flavorings - Beat 2 minutes, Add egg and beat 2 more minutes, Pour over fruit, Bake at 350 for 40 to 50 minutes, Immediately turn upside down on cake plate when taken from oven, Leave pan over cake a few minutes to drain into cake", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from my grandmother (Mamaw)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pistachio Cake", ingredients:"Cake: 1 white cake mix, 1/2 cup milk, 1/2 cup water, 1/2 cup oil, 2 pkgs instant pistachio pudding, 1 envelope Dream Whip, 5 eggs. Frosting: 1 pkg instant Pistachio pudding, 1 envelope Dream Whip, 1 1/2 cups cold milk", directions:"Cake: Blend first 6 ingredients, Then add eggs one at a time, Beat 2 to 3 minutes, Bake in a well greased bundt pan at 350 for 50 - 55 minutes, Let cool a few minutes before turning out onto cake plate. Frosting: Whip until stiff enough to spread, Frost entire cake after it is thoroughly cooled. Break out the fat pants girls - this is a good one", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pizza Dough", ingredients:"2 1/2 - 3 cups flour, 1 1/2 tsp sugar, 2 tsp salt, 1 pkg dry yeast, 1 cup very hot tap water, 2 tbls oil", directions:"In large bowl mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast thoroughly, Gradually add hot water and oil - beating 1 minute, Stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough, Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth ( 8 to 10 minutes ), Place in greased bowl turning to grease the top of dough, Cover and let rise until doubled - about 45 minutes, Punch down - cut in half - press into two greased cookie sheets - or roll out to fit, Top with sauce and other toppings as desired, Bake at 425 for 15 to 20 minutes", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Recipe from Matt, Chris and Steve's grandmother.  Lois has used it for years at the Kiddie College."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pork Roast", ingredients:"3 to 4 lb. pork roast, 2 tbls caraway seed, 1/2 cup chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste, garlic powder or garlic cloves if desired", directions:"If you like garlic or can tolerate garlic then poke holes in the roast and stuff garlic cloves in randomly, No garlic cloves?  Then sprinkle garlic powder over all, sprinkle salt & pepper over all, sprinkle caraway seed over all, pour chicken broth into roasting pan beside roast ( in other words don't wash off everything you just sprinkled), Bake in a covered roasting pan at 400 degrees for 1 1/2 hours, I like to use a cooking bag, This is good with some potatoes and carrots cooked right along with it in the same pan", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Recipe that a friend of the family gave to me.  Very good flavor and very tender."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pot Roast", ingredients:"5 - 6 lbs Chuck roast, 2 lbs. carrots, 4 lbs. potatoes, 3 celery stalks, 2 onions, beef boullion or beef broth - 1 can, onion powder, garlic powder", directions:"Peel carrots and cut into 2in chunks, Peel potatoes and leave whole or cut in half, Clean celery and cut into 2in chunks, Peel onion and leave whole or cut in half, Season both sides of roast with onion powder and easy garlic powder, In a heavy roasting pan, put all vegetables in first - evenly distributed, lay roast on top of vegetables, salt & pepper to taste over all, pour beef broth into pan, add enough water to come half way up vegetables, cover with lid or foil, Bake at 350 for 2 hours - removing foil during last 15 minutes, leftovers can be used for vegetable soup or stew, Hint: Use a turkey size cooking bag for easy clean-up", category:"Dinner", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Potato Soup", ingredients:"3 lbs. potatoes (about 5 or 6 large / any type) - washed, peeled and cubed, 1 cup chopped celery, 1 cup chopped onion, 1/2 stick butter, 6 cups water, 1 cup whole milk, salt and pepper to taste, Hint - Instead of water use chicken broth / Instead of whole milk use heavy cream or half and half", directions:"In a large Dutch Oven size pot - melt the butter over a medium heat, Add celery and onion - cook slowly until soft, Add potatoes, Add water (or broth), Cook until potatoes are very soft, Use a potato masher to press randomly through the pot a few times - not too much - you want this chunky, Add milk (or heavy cream), Add salt and pepper to taste, Simmer, stirring often, until thickened, Sliced carrot is good in this soup, too, but we did not have it that way when we were little, Add additional butter if desired.", category:"Dinner", contributor:"This is Steve's all time favorite soup.  When all of 'us' were little and visiting on vacation to one of the aunt's or uncle's homes that meant a lot of people to feed.  I remember having this often."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Poundcake - (using regular cake mix )", ingredients:"1 package yellow cake mix, 1 package instant vanilla pudding ( 4 serving size ), 4 eggs, 1 cup water, 1/3 cup oil", directions:"Combine all ingredients, Beat two minutes, Pour into well greased and floured bundt pan or tube pan, Bake at 350 for 50 to 60 minutes, Cool in pan for 25 minutes before turning out onto cake plate, Glaze: heat ready to spread frosting in pan or microwave and drizzle over top", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Praline Poundcake", ingredients:"1 cup butter, softened, 1/2 cup shortening, 1 pound light brown sugar, 5 eggs, 3 cups unsifted flour, 1/4 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp baking powder, 3/4 cup milk, 2 tsp vanilla, 2 cups chopped pecans, powdered sugar", directions:"Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar in mixer until light and fluffy, Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition, Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together, alternately with milk, Stir in vanilla and nuts, Pour into well greased and floured bundt pan, Place in a cold oven, turn to 300 degrees, Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes, Cake should bounce back when lightly touched with finger, Let stand 5 minutes, then turn out onto rack to cool, Before serving sift powdered sugar over top if desired", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pumpkin Roll- Grandpa Mock's", ingredients:"Roll: 3 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tsp cinnamon, 3/4 cup flour, 1/4 tsp salt, 1 tsp baking soda, 2/3 cup pumpkin. Filling: 2 tbls butter, 8 oz. cream cheese, 3/4 tsp vanilla, 1 cup powdered sugar", directions:"Roll: Blend together - wet, Blend together - dry, Mix both sets of ingredients together, Then add pumpkin, Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake @350 for 15 minutes, Dump out onto a tea towel sprinkled with powdered sugar, Roll it up from the long side while still warm, Let cool -- while you make the filling. Filling: Unroll and remove cake from towel - spread filling to edges - re-roll and dust with powdered sugar - store in foil wrap", category:"Dessert", contributor:"'Fuzz' used to make this for his family to enjoy."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Pumpkin Roll", ingredients:"Roll: 3 eggs, 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup flour, 1/2 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 tsp ground cloves, 1/4 tsp salt, 2/3 cup pumpkin, 1 cup chopped walnuts ( optional - sprinkle on before baking). Filling: 8 oz cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar, 6 tbls butter, 1 tsp vanilla", directions:"Roll: In a separate bowl mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt, Blend together eggs and sugar - then add dry ingredients - then add pumpkin, Spread on a greased 15 x 10 pan - sprinkle with walnuts if desired, Bake at 350 for 15 minutes, Turn out onto a powder sugar covered tea towel and roll it up while still warm - let cool. Filling: Unroll and remove towel - spread with filling to edges - reroll - sprinkle with powdered sugar - wrap in foil - chill", category:"Dessert", contributor:"(Libby's brand - online recipe)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Red Velvet Cake", ingredients:"Cake: 1 bottle ( 1 oz. ) Red food coloring, 2 tsp vanilla, 2 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1 tsp baking soda, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 cup butter ( 2 sticks ) softened, 2 cups sugar, 4 eggs, 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup milk. Frosting: 8 oz cream cheese, 4 tbls butter, 2 tbls sour cream, 2 tsp vanilla, 1 lb. powdered sugar", directions:"Cake: Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt - set aside, Beat butter and sugar 5 to 7 minutes until light and fluffy, Beat in eggs one at a time, Mix in sour cream, milk, food coloring and vanilla, Gradually beat in flour mixture - just until blended, Bake in two well greased and floured 9in pans at 350 for 35 to 40 minutes. Frosting: Beat until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).  Must be refrigerated.", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Mary's favorite."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Rolls", ingredients:"1 tbsp dry yeast, 1 cup milk scalded, 2 tbsp shortening or oil (grandma uses cooking oil), 2 tbsp sugar, 1 tsp salt, 1 well beaten egg, 3 1/2 cups sifted enriched flour", directions:"soften active dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (110 degrees), combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt - cool to lukewarm, add yeast, add egg, gradually stir in flour to form a soft dough, beat vigorously, cover (with a damp cloth), let rise in a warm place(about 82 degrees) till double, turn out on lightly floured surface, dough has risen once, roll or pat on lightly floured surface till 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick, cut with 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter (or wide mouth quart jar), brush each of the rounds with very soft butter (or melted), make a crease just off center with back of knife, fold so top overlaps slightly, seal end edges, place on greased cookie sheet, brush with melted butter, let rolls rise till double, bake in hot oven - 400 degrees about 15 minutes - makes about 3 dozen small rolls", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"Letter from Mandi ( Steve's friend) 'I finally got my grandma's roll recipe from her.  They're awesome, she makes 12 pans at Thanksgiving every year and not once has one ever lasted long enough to be a left over.  Love, Mandi'"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Rosettes", ingredients:"1 cup flour, 1 cup milk, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 to 3 tsp sugar, 1 egg", directions:"Blend all together, Heat about 2in oil in pan on stovetop, Choose Rosette iron shape and attach to handle, Hold Rosette mold in oil to get hot, Then dip into batter being careful to not dip over top of mold, Hold in hot oil to fry - Rosette will come away from mold and continue frying while you dip another, Use a long fork to flip Rosettes over in oil, Fry to golden brown, Drain on Paper towels, Dust with powdered sugar while still hot", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Royal Icing", ingredients:"1/2 cup plus 1 tablespoon meringue powder ( it may also be labeled dry egg whites), 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons warm water, 12 cups powdered sugar, 3/4 teaspoon cream of tartar", directions:"Combine all ingredients in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a whisk attachment, Start on slow speed and whisk the mixture - as it comes together - increase the speed, Mix for 6 to 8 minutes or until fluffy and shiny - scrape down bowl about halfway through, Keep covered with a damp towel until ready to use, You can thin it with additional warm water or thicken it with additional powdered sugar as needed for project, If using for piping it should be thinned to the consistency of molasses", category:"Dessert", contributor:"This recipe yields 6 cups of frosting so if you don't need that much cut it in half, It can be used to decorate gingerbread houses or cookies - it hardens fast"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Rugelach Cookies  (pronounced roo-geh-la)", ingredients:"8 oz cream cheese, 1/2 lb. butter ( 2 sticks ), 1/4 cup sugar plus 9 tbls sugar, 1/4 tsp salt, 1 tsp vanilla, 2 cups flour, 1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar, 1 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 3/4 cup raisins, 1 cup finely chopped walnuts, 1/2 cup apricot preserves, 1 egg beaten with 1 tbl milk for egg wash", directions:"Cream the cheese and butter, Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt and vanilla, Add flour just until blended, Dump out onto floured board and round up into a ball, Cut ball into 4 pieces, wrap each and chill for 1 hour, Make filling using 6 tbls sugar, the brown sugar, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, the raisins and the walnuts, On a well floured board, roll dough into a 9in circle.  Spread the dough with 2 tbls apricot preserves, Sprinkle on 1/2 cup of the sugar, raisin & nut mixture-pressing it into the apricot & dough, Cut the circle into 12 equal wedges - start at wide edge of each and roll up, Place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper - points tucked under, Chill 30 minutes (helps to make it flaky), Brush with egg wash and sprinkle with combination of 3 tbls sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon, Bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown", category:"Dessert", contributor:"This recipe is for traditional filling - optional fillings would be raspberry w/ nuts and mini choc. chips or just cinnamon sugar and nuts"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Salted Peanut Chews", ingredients:"Base: 1 pkg yellow cake mix, 1/3 cup margarine ( about 5 1/2 tbls ), 1 egg, 3 cups miniature marshmallows. Topping: 2/3 cup corn syrup, 1/4 cup margarine, 2 tsp vanilla, 12 oz pkg peanut butter chips, 2 cups rice krispies, 2 cups salted peanuts", directions:"Combine cake mix, margarine and egg - mix until crumbly, Press into ungreased 9 x 13 pan, Bake at 350 for 12 to 18 minutes until golden, Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle mini marshmallows over the entire top, Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes just until marshmallows begin to puff, Cool while preparing topping, In large saucepan - heat corn syrup, margarine, vanilla and chips, Heat just until chips are melted and mixture is smooth - stirring constantly, Remove from heat, Stir in cereal and nuts, Immediately spoon over marshmallow base, Cool and cut into bars, Good with an additional chocolate drizzle, too.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Sausage Gravy, Chipped Beef, S.O.S., Creamed Tuna", ingredients:"1 lb breakfast sausage - in the tube package, 3 tbls flour, 4 cups milk, 2 cups water - may need more or less, salt & pepper to taste", directions:"Sausage Gravy: Crumble the sausage into a large skillet and cook over medium heat.  Stir through constantly to keep it crumbled, When thoroughly cooked through then sprinkle flour over sausage and blend, Immediately add milk then 1/2 of the water.  It will be thin to start with.  Cook over low heat.  It will thicken as it cooks.  Add more water if needed.  Allow to simmer for a bit to cook the flour.  Add salt & pepper to taste. Chipped Beef: Same recipe - just use one small package of Armor dried beef, finely minced, heat in 1 stick of butter, All other instructions the same. Serve on top of toast slices. S.O.S: This is an old Army recipe.  Same as sausage recipe except you use 1lb. ground beef, Serve on top of toast slices. Creamed Tuna: Aunt Joan used to make this.  Same recipe except use the tuna packed in oil, make the gravy, serve on top of toast slices", category:"Breakfast", contributor:"When we were little and went on vacation to visit our cousins this was always on the menu.  There is nothing like 'biscuits and gravy' with some fried apples, bacon, sausage and eggs. The gravy was always made in the same pan that the sausage was fried in - just grease and flour and milk. Now I make it a little heartier so here is my version."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Schaum cookies", ingredients:"2 or 3 egg whites, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 tsp cream of tartar", directions:"Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, Add sugar slowly while still whipping, Add cream of tartar while still whipping, Beat again until stiff peaks form, Line baking pans with parchment paper or release foil (do not grease), Fill a pastry bag with star tip or fill a large ziplock bag and snip the corner, Now the fun begins, You can make little stars (splotches) all over the pan, close together, then sprinkle with non-pareils, You can make wreaths, You can make swans, Whatever shapes you want as long as they are small and not too thick, Set oven to about 175 to 200, Bake about 45 minutes then turn oven off - leave cookies in for about two hours, These are similar to the meringue cookies that you are paying a fortune for in the stores, Cocoa powder can be added in the first mix for chocolate version.", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Occasionally recipes call for egg yolks only so I make these with the whites that are left over."),
Recipe.create!(name:"Seven Layer Salad", ingredients:"6 cups chopped lettuce , 6 hard boiled eggs - crumbled, 2 cups frozen peas - thawed, 8 to 16 ounces of bacon - cooked crisp, drained and crumbled, 2 cups shredded mild cheddar cheese, 1 cup mayonnaise, 1 to 2 tbls sugar (traditional recipe but okay to exclude if you need sugar free), 1/4 cup green onion including green part - chopped", directions:"Assembly: 3 cups lettuce, eggs overall, 3 cups lettuce, peas overall, bacon overall, cheddar cheese overall, spread mayo mixture overall, garnish with green onion, You can salt and pepper the lettuce and the eggs before layering if desired", category:"Side Dish", contributor:"If you layer this in a clear bowl the presentation is very pretty."),
Recipe.create!(name:"7-UP Salad", ingredients:"7 oz of  7-up, 2 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows, 2 small packages of cream cheese (room temperature), 1 small box of lime Jell-O, a few drops of green food coloring, 1 tbl lemon juice, 2 1/2 cups crushed pineapple (undrained), 3/4 cup chopped walnuts, 1 package Dream Whip", directions:"In a double boiler, combine marshmallows and 7-Up and let melt, Add Jell-O until dissolved, add cream cheese to hot mixture, add lemon juice, pineapple food coloring and nuts, chill until partly set, fold in whipped Dream Whip and chill, Serve alone or with Cool Whip on top, Hint: No double boiler?  Set a heavy glass bowl or stainless steel bowl over a pan of low boiling water, ", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from Jeremy and Ashley's grandmother (Mary used to make it when they were little)"),
Recipe.create!(name:"7-UP Salad", ingredients:"Base: 2 cups boiling water, 2 - 3 oz. packages lemon Jell-O, 12 oz. Seven-Up, 3 bananas - sliced, 1 - 20 oz can crushed pineapple ( drained but save the juice for the topping ), 2 cups mini marshmallows. Topping: 2 tbls margarine, 1 slightly beaten egg, 2 tbls flour, 1 - 8 oz. pkg cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 - 8 oz. pkg Cool Whip, 1/2 cup pineapple juice, Coconut and chopped nuts to garnish", directions:"Base: Add boiling water to Jell-O and stir to dissolve, Add seven-up, Chill until syrupy, Stir in bananas, pineapple and marshmallows, Pour into approximately 9 x 13 glass dish and chill until firm. Topping: Heat butter, flour, sugar, pineapple juice and egg until thick - stirring constantly, Remove from heat and allow to cool down, Beat in cream cheese, Fold in Cool Whip, Spread onto Jell-O layer, Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts liberally over entire top, I like to double the topping recipe", category:"Dessert", contributor:"Recipe from Faye Stepp 1972"),
Recipe.create!(name:"Soft Sugar Cookies", ingredients:"1 cup margarine (keeps cookies softer, longer than butter), 1 1/2 cups granulated sugar, 2 eggs, 1 tsp vanilla, 1tsp baking soda, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp salt, 3/4 cup sour cream, 4 cups all purpose flour", directions:"Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy, beat in eggs and vanilla, mix well, In a separate bowl mix dry ingredients, add to wet mixture alternately with sour cream until blended, chill until firm enough to roll out - a couple of hours, Roll out on lightly floured board - 1/8 inch to 1/4 inch thick, Use cookie cutters or biscuit cutter to cut out cookies, Bake at 350 on ungreased cookie sheets for  about 15 minutes or until edges are light brown, Cool on wire rack, Decorate with sugars before baking or with icings after baking", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Snowball Cookies", ingredients:"1 1/2 cups (3 sticks) butter, softened, 3/4 cup powdered sugar, 1 tbl vanilla, 1/2 tsp salt, 3 cups flour, 1 3/4 cups (10oz package) Nestle Toll House Holiday Shapes and Morsels, 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts, Powdered sugar to sprinkle", directions:"Preheat oven to 375, Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until creamy, Add flour and stir until just blended (not too long), Stir in morsels and nuts, Shape into 1in balls, Bake 10 to 12 minutes (light brown), Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.", category:"Dessert", contributor:""),
Recipe.create!(name:"Spaghetti Sauce", ingredients:"1/4 cup olive oil, 1 cup chopped onion, 3 lbs. ground beef, dash of salt and pepper, 3 large cans tomato sauce (approx. 29 oz size), 1 large can tomato paste, 1 tsp garlic powder, 1 tsp oregano  (or use Italian seasoning for oregano and basil), 1 tsp basil, 1/2 tsp sugar, salt and pepper to taste", directions:"In a large heavy pot (dutch oven size) add the olive oil, onion, ground beef and salt/pepper dashes, Brown slowly so that the onions sweat and get soft, Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste, spices, sugar, salt and pepper, Simmer for at least 30 minutes (preferrably an hour or longer), Traditionally (and the way mom did it) you would simmer this all day to give it a deep rich flavor, If you have six kids and a loaf of Italian bread on the counter then you better lock the lid or there won't be any left. Scilian style would be all the same except you would brown beef short ribs with the onions then add other, ingredients and simmer until thickened.  Serve meat as a side dish and serve smooth sauce with your pasta.", category:"Dinner", contributor:"Janet's, I've learned along the way that a Tuscan style sauce (or gravy as the Italians call it) is the thick meaty kind. Scicilian style is like a marinara with the meat and bones steeped in it for flavor and removed before serving. This recipe is what mom always made (Tuscan style)."),
